==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tampion
<hw>Tam"pi*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>tampon</ets>, <ets>tapon</ets>, <ets>tape</ets>, of Dutch or German
origin. See <er>Tap</er> a pipe or plug, and cf. <er>Tamp</er>,
<er>Tampop</er>, <er>Tompion</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>tampeon</asp>, and <asp>tompion</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
wooden stopper, or plug, as for a cannon or other piece of ordnance,
when not in use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A plug for upper end of an organ
pipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tampoe</ent>⟦br⟧
